OL,7,FAttention had focused on a statement
OL,8,Fby deputy national security adviser
OL,9,F(DNSA) Matt Collins, with prosecutors
OL,10,Fsaying his refusal to describe Beijing
OL,11,Fas a "threat" to national security
OL,12,Fmeant the case could not continue.
OL,14,FMr Collins told the JCNSS he had
OL,15,Fprovided evidence of a "range of
OL,16,Fthreats" posed by China but had not
OL,17,Fdescribed the country as a "generic"
OL,18,Fthreat because that was not the
OL,19,Fposition of the then-Tory government.
